---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Markdown Cheatsheet ‚Äî AI Basics">
  <div class="page">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="header">
      <div class="header-left">
        <div class="series-tag">AI Basics ‚Äî Issue 01</div>
        <h1>Markdown<br><em>Cheatsheet</em></h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Everything you need. Nothing you don't.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="header-right">
        <div class="big-label">Lost In AI Land</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Headings -->
    <div class="section-title">Headings</div>
    <div class="col-labels">
      <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ you type</div>
      <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ renders as</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
      <div class="card-body">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="raw"><span class="sym">#&nbsp;</span><span class="val">Heading 1</span></div>
          <div class="rendered"><h1r>Heading 1</h1r></div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="raw"><span class="sym">##&nbsp;</span><span class="val">Heading 2</span></div>
          <div class="rendered"><h2r>Heading 2</h2r></div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="raw"><span class="sym">###&nbsp;</span><span class="val">Heading 3</span></div>
          <div class="rendered"><h3r>Heading 3</h3r></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Emphasis + Lists -->
    <div class="grid">
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Emphasis</div>
        <div class="col-labels">
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ you type</div>
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ renders as</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="raw"><span class="sym">**</span><span class="val">bold</span><span class="sym">**</span></div>
              <div class="rendered"><strong>bold</strong></div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="raw"><span class="sym">*</span><span class="val">italic</span><span class="sym">*</span></div>
              <div class="rendered"><em>italic</em></div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="raw"><span class="sym">~~</span><span class="val">strikethrough</span><span class="sym">~~</span></div>
              <div class="rendered"><s>strikethrough</s></div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="raw"><span class="sym">`</span><span class="val">inline code</span><span class="sym">`</span></div>
              <div class="rendered"><code>inline code</code></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Lists</div>
        <div class="col-labels">
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ you type</div>
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ renders as</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="raw" style="flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-start;gap:2px;">
                <div><span class="sym">- </span><span class="val">Apples</span></div>
                <div><span class="sym">- </span><span class="val">Oranges</span></div>
                <div><span class="sym">- </span><span class="val">Bananas</span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="rendered">
                <ul><li>Apples</li><li>Oranges</li><li>Bananas</li></ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="raw" style="flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-start;gap:2px;">
                <div><span class="sym">1. </span><span class="val">First</span></div>
                <div><span class="sym">2. </span><span class="val">Second</span></div>
                <div><span class="sym">3. </span><span class="val">Third</span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="rendered">
                <ol style="padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;"><li>First</li><li>Second</li><li>Third</li></ol>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Link + Blockquote + Divider -->
    <div class="grid grid-3">
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Link</div>
        <div class="col-labels">
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ you type</div>
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ renders</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="row" style="flex-direction:column;">
              <div class="raw" style="font-size:11px;word-break:break-all;"><span class="sym">[</span><span class="val">text</span><span class="sym">](url)</span></div>
              <div class="rendered" style="padding:10px 14px;"><a href="#">text</a></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Blockquote</div>
        <div class="col-labels">
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ you type</div>
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ renders</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="row" style="flex-direction:column;">
              <div class="raw"><span class="sym">&gt; </span><span class="val">A quote</span></div>
              <div class="rendered" style="padding:10px 14px;"><blockquote>A quote</blockquote></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Divider</div>
        <div class="col-labels">
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ you type</div>
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ renders</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="row" style="flex-direction:column;">
              <div class="raw"><span class="sym">---</span></div>
              <div class="rendered" style="padding:14px;"><span class="hr-line"></span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Front Matter -->
    <div class="section-title" style="margin-top: 8px;">Front Matter ‚Äî The Hidden Label</div>
    <div class="fm-card">
      <div class="fm-header">
        <span>example.md</span>
        <span>metadata block ¬∑ lives at the very top</span>
      </div>
      <div class="fm-body">
        <div><span class="fm-delim">---</span></div>
        <div><span class="fm-key">title</span>: <span class="fm-val">"What Is a Markdown File?"</span></div>
        <div><span class="fm-key">author</span>: <span class="fm-val">"Josh"</span></div>
        <div><span class="fm-key">date</span>: <span class="fm-val">"2025-01-15"</span></div>
        <div><span class="fm-key">tags</span>: <span class="fm-arr">["basics", "markdown", "AI"]</span></div>
        <div><span class="fm-key">published</span>: <span class="fm-val">true</span></div>
        <div><span class="fm-delim">---</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="fm-explainer">
      <div class="fm-note">
        <div class="fm-note-key">title / author / date</div>
        <div class="fm-note-val">Used by publishing platforms to display metadata without reading the full document.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fm-note">
        <div class="fm-note-key">tags</div>
        <div class="fm-note-val">How knowledge bases and AI tools categorize and retrieve the file automatically.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Best Practices -->
    <div class="section-title" style="margin-top: 28px;">Best Practices</div>
    <div class="bp-grid">
      <div class="bp-item">
        <div class="bp-icon do">‚úÖ</div>
        <div class="bp-text">
          <strong>One # for your title only</strong>
          <p>Use a single H1 at the top. Use ## and ### for everything below it. Hierarchy matters.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bp-item">
        <div class="bp-icon dont">‚ùå</div>
        <div class="bp-text">
          <strong>Don't skip heading levels</strong>
          <p>Jumping from # to ### confuses readers and breaks how AI tools parse your document.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bp-item">
        <div class="bp-icon do">‚úÖ</div>
        <div class="bp-text">
          <strong>Blank lines between blocks</strong>
          <p>Put a blank line between paragraphs, lists, and headings. It keeps rendering clean and consistent.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bp-item">
        <div class="bp-icon dont">‚ùå</div>
        <div class="bp-text">
          <strong>Don't over-bold</strong>
          <p>Bold is for the most critical words only. If everything is bold, nothing is.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bp-item">
        <div class="bp-icon do">‚úÖ</div>
        <div class="bp-text">
          <strong>Use front matter for AI files</strong>
          <p>Any .md file an AI will read benefits from front matter. Title, purpose, and tags help the model understand context before reading a word.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bp-item">
        <div class="bp-icon do">‚úÖ</div>
        <div class="bp-text">
          <strong>Use backticks for anything technical</strong>
          <p>Wrap file names, commands, and code in `backticks`. It signals to both humans and AI that this is literal text, not prose.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Why LLMs Like Markdown -->
    <div class="section-title" style="margin-top: 28px;">Why LLMs Like Markdown</div>
    <div class="ai-callout">
      <div class="ai-icon">ü§ñ</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Markdown is the native language of AI instruction</h3>
        <p>LLMs don't read the way humans do. They process text as a stream of tokens ‚Äî breaking everything down into chunks and looking for patterns and structure. Markdown gives them exactly that, consistently and predictably.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="llm-grid">
      <div class="llm-item">
        <div class="llm-number">01</div>
        <div class="llm-content">
          <strong>Structure is explicit, not implied</strong>
          <p>A <code>#</code> heading unambiguously signals "this is the most important concept on the page." A bullet point signals "these are discrete, parallel items." The model doesn't have to guess ‚Äî the structure is built into the syntax.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="llm-item">
        <div class="llm-number">02</div>
        <div class="llm-content">
          <strong>Easy to parse, easy to generate</strong>
          <p>Markdown has almost no ambiguity. There are no nested tags, no style attributes, no closing elements to match. That simplicity means models can both read and write it reliably ‚Äî which is why every major LLM defaults to Markdown in its responses.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="llm-item">
        <div class="llm-number">03</div>
        <div class="llm-content">
          <strong>Skills and system prompts are .md files</strong>
          <p>When developers build AI tools ‚Äî including the skill instructions that tell Claude or GPT <em>how</em> to do a specific task ‚Äî those instructions are written in Markdown. The model reads the headers to understand sections, the bullets to understand rules, and the bold text to understand what's critical.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="llm-item">
        <div class="llm-number">04</div>
        <div class="llm-content">
          <strong>Front matter gives context before a single word is read</strong>
          <p>The metadata block at the top of a <code>.md</code> file tells the model what the document is, who wrote it, and what it's for ‚Äî before processing any content. It's the difference between handing someone a labelled folder versus a loose stack of papers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="llm-item">
        <div class="llm-number">05</div>
        <div class="llm-content">
          <strong>Your prompts are already Markdown</strong>
          <p>Every time you use bullet points or headers in a ChatGPT or Claude prompt, you're writing Markdown ‚Äî and the model is parsing that structure as part of understanding your intent. A well-formatted prompt isn't just easier to read. It's easier for the AI to follow.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="llm-item llm-item-accent">
        <div class="llm-number" style="color: #f0a05a;">‚Üí</div>
        <div class="llm-content">
          <strong>The bottom line</strong>
          <p>Markdown became the format of choice for AI not because someone decided it ‚Äî but because it's the simplest format that gives both humans and machines a shared understanding of structure. That's rare. That's why it won.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <div class="footer">
      <div class="footer-left">Lost In AI Land</div>
      <div class="footer-right">AI Basics Series ¬∑ Issue 01 ¬∑ lostinai.substack.com</div>
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
